The lobby was modern with a beautiful fireplace and a good breafast/coffee/drinks bar too.	This is a renovated Marriott with an above average lobby and room.	This hotel was a nicer style than most and ranked up there with the downtown waterfront Seattle Marriott for style and a cool bar to chill at in the lobby.	They were slow to arrive at the lobby on Saturday afternoon, evening and the next morning.	The hotel lobby was very spacious, and well furnished with comfy seating for tired travellers to wait while checking-in.	In the lobby there is a lounge area surrounding a free standing fireplace that is enjoyable to sit around and chat.